ve to raid Behemoth or Grummus anymore (failed on both several times), some misgivings that my previous flags already earned is totally devalued by the change. Then there's the &quot;wasted&quot; effort of semi-completion of the BoT quest (lost several times on the medallions). I do see a need for opening up the 2nd and 3rd tier zones, flagging issues have gutted too many smaller guilds. Hence, I don't advocate dropping the flag abolishment idea completely (selfish... I do want to get into BoT, PoTactics too)  but I don't see much good in allowing unprepared (and under-equipped) level 46 players into places like CoD or PoTactics.<br>
<br>
My own compromise proposal:<br>
1) Abolish flag requirements (yes) to an extent.<br>
2) Place a level 60 restriction on these planes.<br>
3) Anyone having a burning need to get into these planes before 60 need to do the flagging quests.<br>
4) Those already having the flags (before 60) and already in these planes get to keep their access.<br>
<br>
Yes, I do agree to some extent that this might appear elitist but I feel that having a level restriction on these zone would benefit the community. Unfettered access to higher 2nd/3rd tier content zones would be detrimental to the gaming experience for all concerned. If you feel the need to PL twinks there, then getting them flagged first should not be a problem. <p><hr />
