mall guilds IMO.<br>
<br>
As for the difficulties of the raid mobs, I guess my perception is a tad warped as our North American public raids are now in Tower of Solusek, and the Asian ones are in Elementals.  It is possible, just requires coordination and determination.<br>
<br>
As for backflagging, I've made the suggestion that killing a mob for a flag will retro-flag you on all the required flags to get up to that mob as well.  Let's face it, if your guild can kill Solusek (basically 85%+ have every single flag up to that point and kill him), I think it's a pretty safe bet that they can kill the previous mobs... seeing that they did already to get all these flags.  Would certainly free up content for the smaller guilds this way IMO. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.recon-eci.org/profile.php?pid=119">Sage Aledar Boomcaster</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
Arcanist of <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.recon-eci.org">Reconstructed</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, E'ci<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.seas.upenn.edu/~bwa/bunnypet.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ravilicuslolf>Ravilicus LoLF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 661<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/03 9:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Acceptable Compromises to Flag Removal</span><hr size=1> Flag removal is a horrible idea.<br>
<br>
It completely removes the plotline from the PoP expansion, and introduces further imbalance to character advancement by allowing level 46 characters to access zones designed for lvl 61+ characters.<br>
<br>
Xarinthus has made excellent points, and provided a sound alternative solution.<br>
<br>
This is EVERQUEST.  There SHOULD be some questing and/or &quot;boss&quot; mob conquering involved in attaining access to some zones.  If they want to make this less stressful on &quot;casual&quot; players and the like, make ALL items used in the alternative flagging quests droppable.  Then the &quot;casual&quot; players can simply shop in the bazaar and pay their dues to other players that do the work for them.<br>
<br>
My level 65 Wizard has 136 AA points, a selo's speed Drogmor, his epic, and some pretty decent pre-Vex Thall gear.  The only tier 3 zone I am currently flagged for is BoT, yet I still want to EARN my flag to Tactics, HoH, Decay, Nightmare B, etc.  As things currently exist in the game, I know it is just a matter of time before I gain access to more zones, and I am content with the requirements to earn this access.<br>
<br>
All they need to do is pique the flag and key quests alittle, make the items used in these quests droppable, decrease respawn times on ALL mobs in ALL zones by 25%+ across the board, and tweak experience rewards so that there isn't so great an incentive for grouping exclusively in PoP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vaeldayanie>vaeldayanie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 41<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/03 9:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Acceptable Compromises to Flag Removal</span><hr size=1> Dropping the flag requirement is possibly the worst idea in recent EQ.  <br>
<br>
The whole point of PoP was that it was supposed to be linear and require hard work to get through.  Instead what they did was cause me to waste a lot of time and deaths getting flags that it turns out I didnt need.  I know some will say, &quot;Well you would've needed the flags for elemental access anyway,&quot; but that point does not hold water.  In a few more months, the same people that bitched to get all these zones opened up to everyone will complain and try to get the elementals opened up for everyone too.  I doubt that it will happen, but that is still the case.<br>
<br>
I am really interested in knowing what the heck bone SoE is going to throw me for my 23 trial passes (not to mention countless failures), my HoH, PoTorment, BoT, PoNB, and CoD flags.  See the difference here is that while all the &quot;casual players&quot; in family guilds were out spending there time doing whatever they wanted in EQ, I was out getting flagged and helping to back flag my fellow guildies.  I wonder what that time is worth to SoE?  Will it get me a cloth cap?  The basic point there is:  1) If you want to see more of PoP either develop more aggressive in game goals for your guild, devote the time to recruiting, exping, farming, and raiding, 2) join a guild that already does this if your current guild shows no signs of moving in this direction, or 3) STFU and realize that without time and effort you get nothing in EQ.<br>
<br>
I am willing to bet that all this stems from SoE's realization that UBER guilds may be leaving soon and much of the casual fan base is getting bored with content.  I am sure it is a business decision on their part.  The shitty thing is that every fucking player that buys a copy of PoP from now on gets the benefit as the same zones as me, without the time and effort.<br>
<br>
Maybe next they will remove the key requirement to VT to help casual guilds gear up for RZtW, or Sol Ro, or maybe get rid of elemental flags altogether.  In any case taking the accomplishments of many and making them trivial to all is a really shitty thing to do.<br>
<br>
Vael <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heofmanyfals>HeOfManyFals</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 461<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/12/03 9:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Acceptable Compromises to Flag Removal</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I don't think there are many people that would disagree with the statement that getting rid of the flag requirements on so many zones is a BAD idea.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
